rson breathing particles into the air. Bold text reads, &quot;wear a mask, protect the NHS.&quot;\" class=\"wp-image-13169\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.56.16\u202fPM.png?w=1476&amp;ssl=1 1476w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.56.16\u202fPM.png?resize=300%2C298&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.56.16\u202fPM.png?resize=1024%2C1017&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.56.16\u202fPM.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.56.16\u202fPM.png?resize=768%2C763&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.56.16\u202fPM.png?resize=70%2C70&amp;ssl=1 70w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"13170\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/_coronadiary\/screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10-55-47-pm\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?fit=1472%2C1458&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1472,1458\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Long Covid is not in your head by Dominque Jackson\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?fit=300%2C297&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?fit=800%2C792&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"792\" data-id=\"13170\"  src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?resize=800%2C792&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"an illustration of a brown woman with her head in her palm disappointed. Bold text reads Long Covid is not in your head \" class=\"wp-image-13170\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?w=1472&amp;ssl=1 1472w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?resize=300%2C297&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?resize=1024%2C1014&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?resize=768%2C761&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/Screenshot-2024-04-09-at-10.55.47\u202fPM.png?resize=70%2C70&amp;ssl=1 70w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In March 2020, Monique Jackson was infected with COVID-19 and has been experiencing symptoms of Long Covid ever since. In her project, <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.stillillcoronadiary.com\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.stillillcoronadiary.com\/\" target=\"_blank\">Corona Diary<\/a>, Jackson documents her story of living with the chronic illness in the UK. She published frequent illustrations that promoted self-advocacy, community building, and helpful resources. Her work has been featured in <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.stillillcoronadiary.com\/new-page\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.stillillcoronadiary.com\/new-page\" target=\"_blank\">news coverage<\/a> and made Jackson a community representative for people experiencing the same symptoms as her. Jackson used art to show people experiencing the isolating process of living with a newly discovered illness that they were not actually alone. Jackson became a facilitator of<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/covid-cafe\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/covid-cafe\/\" target=\"_blank\"> Covid Caf\u00e9 drop-in sessions<\/a> creating a grounding safe spaces for people with shared lived experiences of chronic illness. Using cartoon-style illustrations and humor, Jackson created a validating <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/_coronadiary\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/_coronadiary\/\" target=\"_blank\">visual vocabulary for her life with Long Covid<\/a> that is radical and vulnerable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>-Stephanie Farmer<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>In March 2020, Monique Jackson was infected with COVID-19 and has been experiencing symptoms of Long Covid ever since. In her project, Corona Diary, Jackson documents her story of living with the chronic illness in the UK. 